#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:3
msgid "Solidity Brand Guide"
msgstr "Solidity 品牌名稱"

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:5
msgid ""
"This brand guide features information on Solidity's brand policy and logo "
"usage guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:9
msgid "The Solidity Brand"
msgstr "Solidity 品牌"

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:11
msgid ""
"The Solidity programming language is an open-source, community project "
"governed by a core team. The core team is sponsored by the `Ethereum "
"Foundation <https://ethereum.foundation/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:15
msgid ""
"This document aims to provide information about how to best use the Solidity "
"brand name and logo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:18
msgid ""
"We encourage you to read this document carefully before using the brand name "
"or the logo. Your cooperation is highly appreciated!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:22
msgid "Solidity Brand Name"
msgstr "Solidity 品牌名稱"

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:24
msgid ""
"\"Solidity\" should be used to refer to the Solidity programming language "
"solely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:27
msgid "Please do not use \"Solidity\":"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:29
msgid "To refer to any other programming language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:31
msgid ""
"In a way that is misleading or may imply association of unrelated modules, "
"tools, documentation, or other resources with the Solidity programming "
"language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:35
msgid ""
"In ways that confuse the community as to whether the Solidity programming "
"language is open-source and free to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:39
msgid "Solidity Logo License"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:41
msgid "Creative Commons License"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:45
msgid ""
"The Solidity logo is distributed and licensed under a `Creative Commons "
"Attribution 4.0 International License <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/"
"by/4.0/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:48
msgid ""
"This is the most permissive Creative Commons license and allows reuse and "
"modifications for any purpose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:51
msgid "You are free to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:53
msgid "**Share** — Copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:55
msgid ""
"**Adapt** — Remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose, "
"even commercially."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:58
msgid "Under the following terms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:60
msgid ""
"**Attribution** — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the "
"license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable "
"manner, but not in any way that suggests that the Solidity core team "
"endorses you or your use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:65
msgid ""
"When using the Solidity logo, please respect the Solidity logo guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:68
msgid "Solidity Logo Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:73
msgid "*(Right click on the logo to download it.)*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:75
msgid "Please do not:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:77
msgid "Change the ratio of the logo (do not stretch it or cut it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:79
msgid "Change the colors of the logo, unless it is absolutely necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:82
msgid "Credits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../brand-guide.rst:84
msgid ""
"This document was, in parts, derived from the `Python Software Foundation "
"Trademark Usage Policy <https://www.python.org/psf/trademarks/>`_ and the "
"`Rust Media Guide <https://www.rust-lang.org/policies/media-guide>`_."
msgstr ""
